# .env.example
#
# Template for environment variables read by the application.
# Copy this file to .env and fill in real values for local development.
# The real .env is gitignored and must never be committed.
#
# v1 local has no required environment variables.
# This file exists as a placeholder for the AWS deployment phase,
# where database connection strings, secrets, and config flags
# will be injected via environment.